abstract: >
  BrowseTrace is a public HTTP-request-level benchmark of browser-mediated
  AI-agent web traffic. It captures 1,301 sessions: 400 scripted-random
  sessions across four geographic regions and 901 LLM-driven sessions
  across six models from five providers (OpenAI GPT-4.1-mini, Google
  Gemini 2.5 Flash and Pro, Anthropic Claude Haiku 4.5, DeepSeek-V3.2,
  Alibaba Qwen 2.5-Coder 7B). The release ships stitched cache-replay
  CSVs that reproduce the paper's cache-policy numbers under libCacheSim
  (37.4% LRU vs 59.5% GDSF at 5 MiB on scripted traffic; 43.5% vs 76.2%
  on LLM traffic).
